## 8️⃣ Error Response Handling

Standardize how you handle API errors:

```javascript
// The error.response exists only when server responded (4xx, 5xx)
// error.request exists when no response received (network error)
const handleApiError = (error) => {
  if (error.response) {
    // Server responded with error
    const { status, data } = error.response
    return data.error || `Error ${status}`
  } else if (error.request) {
    // Request made but no response
    return 'Network error — check your connection'
  } else {
    return error.message
  }
}
```

---

## 9️⃣ Pagination & Filtering

```javascript
function useUsers(page, search) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['users', page, search],
    queryFn: () => api.get('/api/users', {
      params: { page, limit: 10, search }
    }).then(r => r.data)
  })
}

// Backend
app.get('/api/users', async (req, res) => {
  const { page = 1, limit = 10, search } = req.query
  const query = search ? { name: new RegExp(search, 'i') } : {}

  const [users, total] = await Promise.all([
    User.find(query).skip((page - 1) * limit).limit(parseInt(limit)),
    User.countDocuments(query)
  ])

  res.json({ users, total, pages: Math.ceil(total / limit) })
})
```

---

## 💡 Summary

| Concept | Code |
|---|---|
| GET request | `axios.get(url)` |
| POST request | `axios.post(url, body)` |
| Auth header | `Authorization: Bearer ${token}` |
| Axios instance | `axios.create({ baseURL })` |
| Interceptors | Auto-attach tokens / handle 401 |
| React Query | Cache + background refetch |
| CORS | `app.use(cors({ origin: 'http://...' }))` |
| Error handling | `error.response?.data?.error` |
